Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has announced that he will address the recently erupted sex scandal around his personal life in a day or two.Ramaphosa was speaking in parliament on Wednesday ahead of a Question and Answer session in the National Assembly.The deputy president elected to speak about the elephant in the room according to him because he regarded all parliamentarians across party lines as colleagues.&#8220;I do need to take responsibility and be accountable,&#8221; said Ramaphosa.